";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:22:"GameSpot - All Content";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"https://www.gamespot.com/feeds/mashup";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:56:"GameSpot's Everything Feed! All the latest from GameSpot";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"language";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"en-us";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:13:"lastBuildDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 10:08:25 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"item";a:15:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"Cyberpunk 2077 PS5 Pro Update CD Projekt Red Once Said No To Is Almost Here";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:143:"https://www.gamespot.com/articles/cyberpunk-2077-ps5-pro-update-cd-projekt-red-once-said-no-to-is-almost-here/1100-6539252/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1698:"<p>After the PS5 Pro launched, many players wanted a <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/cyberpunk-2077/">Cyberpunk 2077</a> update, but CD Projekt Red<a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/cyberpunk-2077-ps5-pro-patch-not-happening-dev-confirms/1100-6527915/"> originally said it had no plans</a> to use the console’s extra power. Now, in 2026, that has changed thanks to <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/ps5-pros-upgraded-pssr-is-rolling-out-today-here-are-the-first-games-getting-it/1100-6538811/">a major upgrade</a> to the PS5 Pro's PlayStation Spectral Super Resolution upscaling technology. This update arrives on April 8, and CDPR has shared details about the new features players will see when they revisit Night City.</p><p>The first big change is that Cyberpunk 2077 will now have 4K visuals and advanced ray tracing. Kuba Knapik, CDPR's VP global art director, <a href="https://blog.playstation.com/2026/04/07/cyberpunk-2077-playstation-5-pro-enhancements-detailed/">said the studio added</a> BVH8--or 8-way Bounding Volume Hierarchy--to bring more advanced ray-traced lighting, shadows, and reflections to the game. This helps bring the team's original artistic vision to life.</p><p>Players will have three graphics modes to pick from. Ray Tracing Pro turns on all ray tracing features. Performance mode focuses on the highest frame rate. Ray Tracing mode offers a balance between performance and quality, with some ray tracing effects and a target of 60 frames per second.</p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/cyberpunk-2077-ps5-pro-update-cd-projekt-red-once-said-no-to-is-almost-here/1100-6539252/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f/">Continue Reading at GameSpot</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"1100-6539252";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 10:06:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:89:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1601/16018044/4678859-cyberpunk-2077.jpg";s:4:"type";s:10:"image/jpeg";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:91:"Call Of Duty&#039;s Dave Chappelle Skin Shows Where Activision Really Stands On Inclusivity";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:153:"https://www.gamespot.com/articles/call-of-dutys-dave-chappelle-skin-shows-where-activision-really-stands-on-inclusivity/1100-6539248/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2409:"<p dir="ltr">It's almost that time of year again, when every corporate entity temporarily gives its logo a rainbow makeover and publicly reaffirms its commitment to inclusivity. But before we get to Pride Month, we have to get through 4/20, which <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/call-of-duty/">Call of Duty</a> is celebrating with a pair of skins depicting Thurgood Jenkins, the fictional character from 1998's Half Baked, played by comedian and noted transphobe Dave Chappelle.</p><p dir="ltr">"There's something going on at Frankencense &amp; Burr Pharmaceutical, and Thurgood Jenkins is right in the middle of it," reads a <a href="https://www.callofduty.com/blog/2026/03/call-of-duty-black-ops-7-season-03-battle-pass-blackcell-store-bundles">recent Activision blog post</a> announcing the upcoming collaboration. "The master of custodial arts takes his chance to have some fun and save a friend, memorialized in this Bundle inspired by the 1998 hit comedy, Half Baked."</p><figure data-align="center" data-size="large" data-img-src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1752/17528202/4678803-thurgoodskins.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-4678803" data-ratio="0.5625" data-width="1280" data-embed-type="image" style="width: 1280px"><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1752/17528202/4678803-thurgoodskins.jpg"><img alt="No Caption Provided" src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1752/17528202/4678803-thurgoodskins.jpg" srcset="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1752/17528202/4678803-thurgoodskins.jpg 1280w, https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1752/17528202/4678803-thurgoodskins.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" data-width="1280"></a></figure><p dir="ltr">I'm old enough to remember the days when Chappelle was known for being funny rather than being a bigot. I grew up watching Chappelle's Show, and like many comedy fans, genuinely enjoyed the guy's work until he started making unfunny jokes about the LGBTQ+ community, with a large amount of vitriol <a href="https://www.salon.com/2021/10/09/dave-chappelle-terf-transphobia-joyce-carol-oates/">aimed at the trans community and female sexual assault victims</a> specifically.</p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/call-of-dutys-dave-chappelle-skin-shows-where-activision-really-stands-on-inclusivity/1100-6539248/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f/">Continue Reading at GameSpot</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"1100-6539248";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 09:37:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:88:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1752/17528202/4678800-thurgoodskins.jpg";s:4:"type";s:10:"image/jpeg";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:83:"This Turn-Based RPG Musical Is Fun But Drags A Bit In Act 3 | People Of Note Review";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:148:"https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/this-turn-based-rpg-musical-is-fun-but-drags-a-bit-in-act-3-people-of-note-review/1900-6418478/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3280:"<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/people-of-note/">People of Note</a> was clearly made with lots of love, but it is also a deeply silly game. Conflicts are resolved between musicians flinging music at each other, a simple country-wide road trip transforms into a battle to save all of reality, and somehow everyone is convinced that the power of friendship will somehow overcome an ancient eldritch-like power. If I didn't know any better, I'd think this game was an old-school role-playing game. And, to be fair, People of Note shares a lot of parallels with those games. While that means the strengths of those types of games are present in People of Note--notably the music and world design in its case--it also means that some of the shortcomings that can be found in the weaker installments of the genre are present in Iridium Studios' turn-based RPG too.</p><p dir="ltr">People of Note sees would-be pop star Cadence striving to fulfill her dream of winning a singing competition and getting propelled into fame. Worried that the pop song she's prepared isn't strong enough to sway the judges, she sets out through the land of Note in search of people who can add to her song. Her journey takes her to a desert where everyone is all about different kinds of rock music, a futuristic metropolis blanketed in perpetual night and inhabited by EDM-obsessed disc jockeys, a block-shaped party city that's all about rap and hip hop, and so much more. And all the while, repeated references to an event known as the Harmonic Convergence steel you for what will eventually be a sharp tonal shift away from road-trip comedy to dramatic high fantasy.</p><figure data-align="center" data-size="large" data-img-src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1587/15875866/4678846-2.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-4678846" data-ratio="0.5625" data-width="1920" data-embed-type="image" style="width: 1920px"><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1587/15875866/4678846-2.jpg"><img alt="No Caption Provided" src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_super/1587/15875866/4678846-2.jpg" srcset="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1587/15875866/4678846-2.jpg 1920w, https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_super/1587/15875866/4678846-2.jpg 1280w, https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1587/15875866/4678846-2.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" data-width="1280"></a></figure><p dir="ltr">Your enjoyment of this story is really going to come down to how much you like puns and pop culture references--People of Note's humor is not unlike Borderlands 2 or Saints Row IV. The game rides the line between funny and corny well enough for me, save for one moment in the third act that made me cringe so hard, I contemplated simply not playing any more of the game that day. But I also enjoy games like Borderlands and Saints Row. If you're not a fan of the idea of a story that takes every single conceivable musical term and crafts a whole high-fantasy society and plotline with said terms, People of Note is probably going to grate.</p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/this-turn-based-rpg-musical-is-fun-but-drags-a-bit-in-act-3-people-of-note-review/1900-6418478/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f/">Continue Reading at GameSpot</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"1900-6418478";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 09:25:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:128:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1587/15875866/4678845-ss_1006d3188578d27cae86642e35dd8f019b6e8636.1920x1080.jpg";s:4:"type";s:10:"image/jpeg";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"Dead As Disco - Exclusive Arora K-Pop Boss Fight Gameplay";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:101:"https://www.gamespot.com/videos/dead-as-disco-exclusive-arora-k-pop-boss-fight-gameplay/2300-6466808/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:199:"<img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_medium/1574/15746725/4678789-11.jpg" width="480" height="480" /> Dead As Disco will be released On Steam and Epic Games Store in Early Access soon.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"2300-6466808";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 09:00:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:77:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1574/15746725/4678789-11.jpg";s:4:"type";s:10:"image/jpeg";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"Pokemon Champions: The Beginner&#039;s Guide To Competitive Pokemon";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:128:"https://www.gamespot.com/articles/pokemon-champions-the-beginners-guide-to-competitive-pokemon/1100-6539154/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2258:"<p dir="ltr">EVs, natures, abilities, priority, secondary effects, damage rolls! Learning competitive Pokemon can be overwhelming. Pokemon Champions is the next phase of serious competitive play, and the free-to-play release on Switch and mobile will be used for competitive events going forward. While the core of Pokemon is meant to be approachable for all ages, competitive Pokemon has quite a bit going on under the hood for serious Pokemon masters. This will serve as a primer for getting into the serious competitive scene to take your Pokemon training to the next level.</p><h3 dir="ltr">Making A Monster Team</h3><p dir="ltr">Competitive Pokemon can be divided into two phases: Team building and battling. Team building is primarily defined by optimizing your Pokemon's base stats. Every Pokemon has six stats: HP, Attack, Defense, Special Attack, Special Defense, and Speed. By looking at a Pokemon’s base stats you can get an idea of how they are played. For example, Charizard’s two highest stats are Speed and Special Attack, while Annihilape has high HP and Attack. Generally speaking, this means Charizard is a fast special attacker and Annihilape is a bulky attacker. Of course, players have found many other uses for these Pokemon, but for simplicity we’re going to treat them as such.</p><p dir="ltr">So what’s the difference between an Attacker and Special Attacker? It largely comes down to its move pool. Moves that deal damage in Pokemon are split into two attack types: Physical and Special. Physical Attacks calculate the users attack stat against the opponent’s Defense Stat. Special attacks calculate the users special attack stat against the opponent's special defense. There is a lot of math that happens here, but the general rule of thumb is that Pokemon with a high attack should only be using physical attacks and a Pokemon with high special attack should only use special attacks. This is denoted by symbols next to the move name. Ideally when team building you’d want to have a mix of attackers and special attackers to cover your bases.</p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/pokemon-champions-the-beginners-guide-to-competitive-pokemon/1100-6539154/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f/">Continue Reading at GameSpot</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"1100-6539154";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 08:32:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:147:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1585/15855271/4676190-4668790-f43ebd5cdac98ed79b9e15c399b87e2c0d354757906f90eb3bd02aa01edc01e8.jpg";s:4:"type";s:10:"image/jpeg";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:83:"Super Mario Galaxy Movie Includes Disclaimer That It Cannot Be Used For AI Training";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:151:"https://www.gamespot.com/articles/super-mario-galaxy-movie-includes-disclaimer-that-it-cannot-be-used-for-ai-training/1100-6539250/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:960:"<p>The Super Mario Galaxy Movie is in theaters now, and it's putting up <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/highest-grossing-video-game-movies-of-all-time/2900-3968/">big numbers at the box office</a>. It's also been discovered that the film ends with a disclaimer about AI.</p><p>The movie's credit sequences includes a line about how the movie "may not be used to train AI."</p><p>This wasn't specific to The Super Mario Galaxy Movie. The movie's distributor, Universal, started attaching this warning to the credits of its movies with June 2025's How to Train Your Dragon, according to <a href="https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/business/business-news/universal-pictures-big-tech-well-sue-if-you-steal-movies-ai-1236337712/">The Hollywood Reporter</a>.</p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/super-mario-galaxy-movie-includes-disclaimer-that-it-cannot-be-used-for-ai-training/1100-6539250/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f/">Continue Reading at GameSpot</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"1100-6539250";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 08:26:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:83:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1179/11799911/4678842-smgmovie.jpg";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:116:"You Could Be In A PlayStation Game If You Write Well, Love PlayStation, Play And Own A Lot, Have Anecdotes, And More";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:207:"https://www.gamespot.com/articles/you-could-be-in-a-playstation-game-if-you-write-well-love-playstation-play-and-own-a-lot-have-shareable-and-entertaining-anecdotes-and-more/1100-6539246/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:904:"<p>PlayStation has announced a new contest called The Playerbase, and it will allow winners to have their likenesses scanned to appear in PlayStation games.</p><p>This begins with Gran Turismo 7, but PlayStation said it will expand the program to include other titles from PlayStation Studios.</p><p>Here's how it works: You can <a href="https://www.playstation.com/en-us/the-playerbase/">visit the Playerbase website</a> where you'll need to submit comments on why PlayStation is important to you. "Make it something from the heart," Sony said. The company will then review applications and choose a "limited" number of people for video interviews.</p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/you-could-be-in-a-playstation-game-if-you-write-well-love-playstation-play-and-own-a-lot-have-shareable-and-entertaining-anecdotes-and-more/1100-6539246/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f/">Continue Reading at GameSpot</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"1100-6539246";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 07:30:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:90:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1179/11799911/4678797-playstationface.jpg";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:55:"New Game Of Thrones Game Officially Revealed For Mobile";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:123:"https://www.gamespot.com/articles/new-game-of-thrones-game-officially-revealed-for-mobile/1100-6539233/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:911:"<p>Warner Bros. Games and HBO have released a new trailer for Game of Thrones: Dragonfire, an upcoming free-to-play mobile game based on the prequel series House of the Dragon.</p><p>A strategy game set 172 years before Daenerys Targaryen was born, Dragonfire is developed by Warner Bros. Games Boston and takes inspiration from events from the TV series. You play as a Valyrian descendant who has to hatch, raise, and fly dragons in battle to dominate Westeros.</p><p>The game features familiar characters from the show--including Rhaenyra Targaryen and Alicent Hightower--as well as original characters created for the game, and like the show, players need to strategize and form alliances to come out on top. Check out the trailer below.</p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/new-game-of-thrones-game-officially-revealed-for-mobile/1100-6539233/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f/">Continue Reading at GameSpot</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"1100-6539233";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 07:00:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:115:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1179/11799911/4678299-screenshot2026-04-06at1.23.54%E2%80%AFpm.png";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:93:"New Game Pass Games For April 2026: Hades 2, Kiln, And Vampire Crawlers Headline A Busy Month";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:134:"https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/new-game-pass-games-for-april-2026-hades-2-kiln-and-vampire-crawlers-headline-a-busy-month/2900-7656/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7107:"    <p><h2>Get ready for wildcards, ice hockey, and pottery deathmatches in April</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678793-vampire-crawlers.jpg" /><br /><p>Microsoft just revealed a new batch of games coming to Xbox Game Pass, and this month is packed. Several day-one releases are on the way, and in between those big launches, you’ll have a chance to catch up on other titles you might have missed.</p><p>One of the biggest highlights is Hades 2, which was only available on PC and Switch 2 when it launched in late 2025. This sequel builds on the first Hades and adds even more depth, rewarding players who experiment and stick with it as they try to defeat the Titan of Time. Other day-one releases include Doublefine’s pottery-themed brawler Kiln, the long-awaited dystopian adventure Replaced, and the deck-building game Vampire Crawlers.</p><p>As always, a few <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/game-pass-games-leaving-soon/2900-7093/">games will leave Game Pass on April 15</a>. Check out the full list of April’s upcoming Game Pass titles below.</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Final Fantasy IV</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678768-ff4.jpg" /><br /><p>Final Fantasy IV will be available through Game Pass Ultimate, Game Pass Premium, and PC Game Pass for cloud, PC, and Xbox Series X|S on April 7. </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>DayZ</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678770-aprilgamepasswave1%2812%29.jpg" /><br /><p>DayZ will be available through Game Pass Ultimate, Game Pass Premium, Game Pass Essential, and PC Game Pass for PC on April 8. </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Endless Legend 2</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678772-aprilgamepasswave1%2811%29.jpg" /><br /><p>Endless Legend will be available through Game Pass Premium starting April 8, also available through Game Pass Ultimate and PC Game Pass for PC.</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>FBC: Firebreak</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678773-aprilgamepasswave1%2810%29.jpg" /><br /><p>FBC: Firebreak will be available through Game Pass Premium starting April 8, also available through Game Pass Ultimate and PC Game Pass for PC.</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Planet Coaster 2</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678774-aprilgamepasswave1%289%29.jpg" /><br /><p>Planet Coaster 2 will be available through Game Pass Ultimate, Game Pass Premium, and PC Game Pass for cloud, PC, and Xbox Series X|S on April 9. </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Tiny Bookshop</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678775-aprilgamepasswave1%288%29.jpg" /><br /><p>Tiny Bookshop will be available through Game Pass Ultimate, Game Pass Premium, and PC Game Pass for cloud, PC, handheld, and Xbox Series X|S on April 10. </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Football Manager 26</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678776-aprilgamepasswave1%287%29.jpg" /><br /><p>Football Manager 26 will be available through Game Pass Premium starting April 13, also available through Game Pass Ultimate and PC Game Pass for PC.</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Football Manager 26 Console</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678777-aprilgamepasswave1%286%29.jpg" /><br /><p>Football Manager 26 Console will be available through Game Pass Premium starting April 13, also available through Game Pass Ultimate and PC Game Pass for PC.</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Hades II</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678778-aprilgamepasswave1%285%29.jpg" /><br /><p>Hades II will be available through Game Pass Ultimate, Game Pass Premium, and PC Game Pass for cloud, PC, handheld, and Xbox Series X|S on April 14.</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Replaced</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678779-aprilgamepasswave1%284%29.jpg" /><br /><p>Replaced will be available through Game Pass Ultimate and PC Game Pass for cloud, PC, and Xbox Series X|S on April 14.</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>The Thaumaturge</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678780-aprilgamepasswave1%283%29.jpg" /><br /><p>The Thaumaturge will be available through Game Pass Ultimate, Game Pass Premium, and PC Game Pass for cloud, PC, and Xbox Series X|S on April 14.</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>The Elder Scrolls IV: Oblivion Remastered</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678781-aprilgamepasswave1%282%29.jpg" /><br /><p>The Elder Scrolls IV: Oblivion Remastered will be available through Game Pass Premium starting April 16, also available through Game Pass Ultimate and PC Game Pass for PC.</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>EA Sports NHL 26</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678769-nhl-26.jpg" /><br /><p>EA Sports NHL 26 will be available through Game Pass Ultimate and PC Game Pass for cloud and Xbox Series X|S on April 16.</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Call of Duty: Modern Warfare</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678783-aprilgamepasswave1%281%29.jpg" /><br /><p>Call of Duty: Modern Warfare will be available through Game Pass Ultimate, Game Pass Premium, and PC Game Pass for cloud, PC, and Xbox Series X|S on April 17.</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Little Rocket Lab</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678784-aprilgamepasswave1%2816%29.jpg" /><br /><p>Little Rocket Lab will be available through Game Pass Premium starting April 21, also available through Game Pass Ultimate and PC Game Pass for PC.</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Sopa: Tale of the Stolen Potato</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678785-aprilgamepasswave1%2815%29.jpg" /><br /><p>Sopa: Tale of the Stolen Potato will be available through Game Pass Premium starting April 21, also available through Game Pass Ultimate and PC Game Pass for PC.</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Vampire Crawlers</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678786-aprilgamepasswave1%2814%29.jpg" /><br /><p>Vampire Crawlers will be available through Game Pass Ultimate and PC Game Pass for cloud, PC, handheld, and Xbox Series X|S on April 21</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Kiln</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678787-aprilgamepasswave1%2813%29.jpg" /><br /><p>Kiln will be available through Game Pass Ultimate and PC Game Pass for cloud, PC, handheld, and Xbox Series X|S on April 23.</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>New Game Pass Essential games</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1601/16018044/4678792-ss_6b459fcf2c685275b0963d056113a23b538d1bdf.1920x1080.jpg" /><br /><p>Game Pass Essential subscribers can grab Warhammer Vermintide 2 (Cloud and Console) and DayZ (PC), starting April 8. </p></p><br/> ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"2900-7656";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 06:52:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:91:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1601/16018044/4678793-vampire-crawlers.jpg";s:4:"type";s:10:"image/jpeg";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:55:"Best Loadouts In Call Of Duty: Warzone For BO7 Season 3";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:98:"https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/best-loadouts-in-call-of-duty-warzone-for-bo7-season-3/2900-7655/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9025:"    <p><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1639/16394540/4678751-season03launchtrailer_callofduty_warzone%26blackops70-52screenshot%281%29.jpg" /><br /><p dir="ltr">Season 3 of <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/call-of-duty-black-ops-7/">Call of Duty: Black Ops 7</a> has arrived in <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/call-of-duty-warzone/">Warzone</a>. The big update brings <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/all-cod-black-ops-7-and-warzone-season-3-weapons-and-how-to-unlock-them/2900-7640/">new guns</a>, more attachments, and some weapon tuning, so you'll likely want to swap out some of the loadouts you used last season. In this guide, we will recommend some of the best weapon builds for Warzone in Season 3.</p><p dir="ltr">Black Ops 7's Gunsmith includes the weapon build code feature. Weapon build codes are unique to each weapon and a specific set of attachments, making it easy to share and receive custom weapon builds. We'll list the attachments for each build, but also include the unique weapon code for you to easily enter and use.</p><p dir="ltr">Simply hit L3 to pull up your options while you are in the Gunsmith. This will let you import a weapon build code to use. Additionally, any weapon builds you create in the Gunsmith will have a code generated at the bottom-left corner of your screen.</p><p dir="ltr">We'll list the attachments for each recommended build and include the unique weapon code so you can easily use it. These recommended weapon builds can be used across standard battle royale and Resurgence mode.</p><p dir="ltr">However, Warzone's Black Ops Royale doesn't use custom loadouts. Instead, we'll recommend some <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/cod-warzone-black-ops-royale-how-to-get-weapons-and-upgrade-them/1100-6538521/">gun archetypes</a> to consider grabbing in your next match.</p><p dir="ltr">All of our recommended Warzone loadouts can be viewed below, and we also have suggested <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/best-loadouts-in-call-of-duty-black-ops-7-for-season-3/2900-7654/">multiplayer loadouts for Season 3</a>.</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>MK35 ISR</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1639/16394540/4678752-mk35isr.jpg" /><br /><p dir="ltr">Season 3's new MK35 ISR is a full-auto assault rifle with low recoil, allowing you to have great accuracy at range. The recommended attachments will boost the gun's bullet velocity and increase the ammo count as well as further reduce the weapon's recoil.</p><h3 dir="ltr">Recommended MK35 ISR attachments:</h3><ul><li dir="ltr"><strong>Optic:</strong> Fang Hoverpoint ELO</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Muzzle:</strong> Monolithic Suppressor</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Barrel:</strong> 16.5" Greaves Bellum Barrel</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Underbarrel: </strong>Vas Convergence Foregrip</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Magazine:</strong> Bowen Siren Drum</li></ul><p dir="ltr"><strong>Build code: </strong>A12-34FK5-DRNJU-11</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>EGRT-17</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1639/16394540/4678753-egrt17.jpg" /><br /><p dir="ltr">Another assault rifle option is the EGRT-17. This is a fairly easy-to-handle assault rifle for long-to mid-range gunfights. The recommended attachments will boost the bullet velocity and reduce the gun's recoil.</p><h3 dir="ltr">Recommended EGRT-17 attachments:</h3><ul><li dir="ltr"><strong>Optic:</strong> Fang Hoverpoint ELO</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Muzzle:</strong> Monolithic Suppressor</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Barrel:</strong> 15" Bowen Resistor Barrel</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Magazine: </strong>Fuel Cell-X3 Mag</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Stock: </strong>Frigate Control Stock</li></ul><p dir="ltr"><strong>Build code:</strong> A07-34FBS-SSUGK-11</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>MK.78</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1639/16394540/4678754-mk78.jpg" /><br /><p dir="ltr">If you want a long-range option with plenty of ammo, the MK.78 light machine gun is a solid option for battle royale. The recommended attachments will boost the bullet velocity as well as reduce much of the gun's recoil.</p><h3 dir="ltr">Recommended MK.78 attachments:</h3><ul><li dir="ltr"><strong>Optic:</strong> Fang Hoverpoint ELO</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Muzzle:</strong> Monolithic Suppressor</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Barrel:</strong> 22" Impulse HB-762 Barrel</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Underbarrel:</strong> VAS Convergence Foregrip</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Stock:</strong> Shock Shield Stock</li></ul><p dir="ltr"><strong>Build code: </strong>L01-2R4XJ-XDNRN-11</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Peacekeeper MK1</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1639/16394540/4678755-peacekeeperrmk1.jpg" /><br /><p dir="ltr">If you're looking for a fast gun to pair with a sniper rifle, the Peacekeeper MK1 assault rifle is a solid pick for sniper support. The recommended attachments will help reduce some of the gun's kick and boost the ammo count.</p><h3 dir="ltr">Recommended Peacekeeper MK1 attachments:</h3><ul><li dir="ltr"><strong>Optic:</strong> Fang Hoverpoint ELO</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Muzzle:</strong> Redwell Shade-X Suppressor</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Barrel: </strong>19.4" Stimulus Barrel</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Magazine:</strong> Vulcan Reach Extension</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Fire Mods: </strong>Buffer Springs</li></ul><p dir="ltr"><strong>Build code:</strong> A06-34FBS-UD7A7-51</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Razor 9MM</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1639/16394540/4678762-bo7-multiplayer-overview-050.jpg" /><br /><p dir="ltr">The Razor 9MM is one of the most-powerful picks for close-range fights for Season 3 of Warzone. The recommended attachments will help reduce recoil as well as improve the gun's ADS speed and sprint-to-fire time.</p><h3 dir="ltr">Recommended Razor 9MM attachments:</h3><ul><li dir="ltr"><strong>Optic:</strong> Lethal Tools ELO</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Muzzle:</strong> Bowen 9MM Suppressor</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Magazine:</strong> Zealot Extended Mag II</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Rear Grip:</strong> Vice Grip</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Stock:</strong> Constrictor Pad</li></ul><p dir="ltr"><strong>Build code:</strong> S03-AUYEX-K3YI-1-1</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>VST</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1639/16394540/4678758-vst.jpg" /><br /><p dir="ltr">Season 3's new VST is a powerful and fast-firing submachine gun, but it does come bundled with some heavy vertical recoil. The recommended attachments will help greatly reduce the VST's recoil and make this a strong choice for close-range fights, especially on the smaller Resurgence maps.</p><h3 dir="ltr">Recommended VST attachments:</h3><ul><li dir="ltr"><strong>Muzzle:</strong> Hawker Series 45</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Barrel:</strong> 10" Bowen Conquer Barrel</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Underbarrel: </strong>Lateral Precision</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Magazine: </strong>Avarice Extended Mag II</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Rear Grip: </strong>VAS Sustenance Grip</li></ul><p dir="ltr"><strong>Build code:</strong> S12-2X3RZ-KN11</p><p> </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Strider 300</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1639/16394540/4678764-strider300.jpg" /><br /><p dir="ltr">Season 3's new Strider 300 overtakes the Hawker HX as the most popular choice for a sniper rifle. The Strider 300 is a powerful bolt-action sniper rifle, but you'll want the recommended attachments to improve the bullet velocity, as well as increase the gun's ADS time and reload speed.</p><h3 dir="ltr">Recommended Strider 300 attachments:</h3><ul><li dir="ltr"><strong>Muzzle: </strong>Monolithic Suppressor</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Barrel:</strong> 25" Bowen Grooved Barrel</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Magazine:</strong> Carnation Fast Mag</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Rear Grip:</strong> Hatch Quick Grip</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Fire Mods:</strong> .300 WM Overpressured</li></ul><p dir="ltr"><strong>Build code:</strong> R07-2JD6P-5NM5G-6J11</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Black Ops Royale best archetypes for Season 3</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1639/16394540/4678767-blackopsroyale1.jpg" /><br /><p dir="ltr">Black Ops Royale doesn't use custom loadouts, so you're limited to ground loot. Each weapon is labelled as a specific archetype, which determines what attachments you'll get when upgrading it up with attachment kits.</p><p dir="ltr">Here are some recommended guns to look for:</p><ul><li dir="ltr"><strong>MK35 ISR assault rifle:</strong> Recon Archetype</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>AK-27 assault rifle:</strong> Recon Archetype</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>MK. 78 LMG:</strong> Heavy-Metal archetype</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Razor 9MM SMG:</strong> Burner Archetype</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Ryden 45K SMG: </strong>Burner Archetype</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>Hawker HX sniper rifle: </strong>Redacted archetype</li></ul></p><br/> ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"2900-7655";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 06:31:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:148:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1639/16394540/4678750-season03launchtrailer_callofduty_warzone%26blackops70-52screenshot%281%29.jpg";s:4:"type";s:10:"image/jpeg";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:10;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"Uncharted 5 Underwent &quot;Some Planning&quot; Years Ago, Report Says";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:125:"https://www.gamespot.com/articles/uncharted-5-underwent-some-planning-years-ago-report-says/1100-6539244/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1312:"<p>Naughty Dog "floated" the possibility of making a new Uncharted game in the years since 2016's Uncharted 4: A Thief's End, according to reporter Tom Henderson. He said on the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?t=2857&amp;v=VZQxeVBBMSA&amp;feature=youtu.be">Insider Gaming podcast</a> that there was "some planning of an Uncharted 5" prior to the COVID-19 pandemic.</p><p>As reported by <a href="https://www.pushsquare.com/news/2026/04/rumour-naughty-dog-floated-the-idea-of-uncharted-5-before-covid">Push Square</a>, Henderson didn't have any further details about these apparently plans or what the story for a fifth Uncharted game might be. Uncharted 4 brought a close to main character Nathan Drake's story, but the game's <a href="https://uncharted.fandom.com/wiki/Epilogue">epilogue</a> showed Cassie, the daughter of Nathan Drake and Elena, with fans theorizing that a future Uncharted game could feature Cassie as the main character.</p><p>In fact, the epilogue of Uncharted 4 had players playing as Cassie, walking through their home and discovering some of her father's artifacts that he himself found on his many journeys.</p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/uncharted-5-underwent-some-planning-years-ago-report-says/1100-6539244/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f/">Continue Reading at GameSpot</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"1100-6539244";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 05:56:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:115:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1179/11799911/4678771-screenshot2026-04-07at9.31.29%E2%80%AFam.png";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:11;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"Blizzard Unveils Anran&#039;s Redesigned Face In Overwatch Season 2";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:129:"https://www.gamespot.com/articles/blizzard-unveils-anrans-redesigned-face-in-overwatch-season-2/1100-6539241/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2089:"<p>Earlier this year, Blizzard received pushback from <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/overwatch/">Overwatch</a> players over the appearance of the new hero, Anran, in part because her in-game appearance too closely resembled other characters on the roster. Blizzard subsequently <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/blizzard-commits-to-changing-new-overwatch-heros-appearance-following-same-face-criticism/1100-6538052/">promised to rework Anran</a>, and now the publisher has unveiled her new face ahead of Season 2. </p><p>Overwatch director Aaron Keller shared Anran's updated appearance online, and noted that some other subtle changes like her posture were modified to make her seem more like a confident and mature leader.</p><div data-embed-type="tweet" data-src="https://x.com/PlayOverwatch/status/2041290205659861214" data-has-image="true"><blockquote align="center" class="twitter-tweet" data-conversation="none" data-mce-disable-toolbar="true"><p dir="ltr">In Season 2, we’re introducing an updated look for Anran. She didn’t fully land as the fiery and fierce sister of Wuyang that we hoped she would. With this update, our team focused on strengthening her overall presence. <br /><br />This evolution reflects both our creative intent and the… <a href="https://t.co/1AwaVDuzdo">pic.twitter.com/1AwaVDuzdo</a></p>  — Overwatch (@PlayOverwatch) <a href="https://twitter.com/PlayOverwatch/status/2041290205659861214?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">April 6, 2026</a></blockquote>          <text></text>    </div><p>"We focused on her eyes, eyebrows, and mouth, and we moved away from that baby face, look, and expression to something more sincere and more mature," said Keller. "Even something like a simple posture change can help Anran feel, well, more like Anran! We're really happy with the way these changes turned out, and also that she has a closer resemblance to her brother Wuyang."</p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/blizzard-unveils-anrans-redesigned-face-in-overwatch-season-2/1100-6539241/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f/">Continue Reading at GameSpot</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"1100-6539241";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 05:53:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:89:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1837/18375603/4678711-overwatchanran.jpg";s:4:"type";s:10:"image/jpeg";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:12;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"Best Crimson Desert Mods To Improve Your Journey Through Pywel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/best-crimson-desert-mods/2900-7650/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9409:"    <p><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1745/17457013/4676706-crimson-desert-new-trailer-gamescom-opening-night-live-2023.png" /><br /><p>There aren't many video game worlds quite like <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/crimson-desert/">Crimson Desert</a>'s thanks to its sprawling open world, and it can become even more expansive and special with the use of mods. Since the launch of Crimson Desert, modders have put their heads down and come up with some truly impressive creations that aim to enhance all levels of the game. From making the world even more pleasurable to explore, to fixing some of the unintuitive controls, to adding new gameplay elements, the sky is the limit for Crimson Desert mods.</p><p>While you can spend your time browsing the entirety of Nexus Mods, we have compiled a list of the best Crimson Desert mods you can download. As the modding community for the game is still being built, however, you can expect even more to become available as time goes on. For now, though, here are the best mods for Crimson Desert.</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Inventory Expander</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1745/17457013/4676715-image_1775143477188.jpg" /><br /><ul><li><strong>Created by</strong>: kindiboy</li><li><strong>Download</strong>: <a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/56">Nexus Mods</a></li></ul><p>It's no secret that the inventory system in Crimson Desert could use some work. While the developer has added a personal storage chest to your camp, that might not be enough when you're out exploring large chunks of the map in a single trip. If you ever find yourself having to ditch valuable items for more inventory space, then downloading the Inventory Expanded mod is a quick and easy solution. It expands the inventory to include 180 total slots by default, but that can be manually upgraded to 999 slots, which is plenty for any player.</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Infinite Stamina</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1745/17457013/4676717-image_1775143845262.jpg" /><br /><ul><li><strong>Created by</strong>: PhorgeForge</li><li><strong>Download</strong>: <a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/107">Nexus Mods</a><a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/56"><br /></a></li></ul><p>Your stamina in Crimson Desert acts as the bane of your existence in Pywel. It's a constant resource that you need to manage in order to survive, which can become a real pain as the game goes on. If you want to get rid of your stamina bar altogether, then download the Infinite Stamina mod. This completely removes stamina from the game, allowing you to run as far as you want, glide for an eternity, and never lose speed on a mount. </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>CDCamera</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1745/17457013/4676718-image_1775143973165.jpg" /><br /><ul><li><strong>Created by</strong>: Maszradine</li><li><strong>Download</strong>: <a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/65">Nexus Mods</a></li></ul><p>For the most part, Crimson Desert is best experienced while using the third person camera. However, there's no option to customize the third person camera through the settings menu. Fortunately, the CDCamera mod gives you a ton of options to make the camera exactly the way you want it. You can change your field of view, camera height and distance, framing, and more.</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Minimap Tweaks</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1745/17457013/4676719-image_1775144037359.jpg" /><br /><ul><li><strong>Created by</strong>: Caites</li><li><strong>Download</strong>: <a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/275">Nexus Mods</a></li></ul><p>The mini map in Crimson Desert is perfectly adequate for trying to navigate the different regions of Pywel and find fast travel points. However, it could be massively improved, and that's what the Minimap Tweaks mod aims to do. With the mod, the fog on the map is revealed at longer ranges, the zooming function is more consistent, and the icons on the map have a larger size when zooming in and out. It's not something game-changing, but it makes the minimap much easier to use.</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>All Ore In Butcher Leather Shop</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1745/17457013/4676720-image_1775144091682.jpg" /><br /><ul><li><strong>Created by</strong>: PLMOST</li><li><strong>Download</strong>: <a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/260">Nexus Mods</a></li></ul><p>While it's a core part of the gameplay loop in Crimson Desert, it can be extremely annoying trying to hunt down all of the rare ores you need to craft and upgrade gear. To ensure you never have to go searching for Epidote or any other ore again, download the All Ore In Butcher Leather Shop mod. This simply stocks the Butcher and Leather shop with all available ores in Crimson Desert, allowing you to purchase them directly. </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Configurable Autoloot</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1850/18507742/4678710-crimson-desert-mods.jpg" /><br /><ul><li><strong>Created by</strong>: Cybergecko1</li><li><strong>Download: </strong><a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/95?tab=description">Nexus Mods</a><a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/14"><br /></a></li></ul><p>With the sheer amount of loot available in Crimson Desert, it can get tedious checking every container, chest, or nearby item. The Configurable Autoloot mod makes it so that you'll automatically interact with nearby items to loot them. Note that this can lead to some unintended behaviors, such as hiding in haystacks or ringing doorbells, although this can be disabled with a little bit of tinkering with the mod's settings and sensitivity. You can also choose to activate and deactivate the mod to suit you, so if you're worried about tarnishing your reputation just toggle it off.</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Abyss in Grocery</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1745/17457013/4676731-image_1775145656333.jpg" /><br /><ul><li><strong>Created by</strong>: PLMOST</li><li><strong>Download</strong>: <a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/303">Nexus Mods</a><a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/14"><br /></a></li></ul><p>If you've ever wanted to just buy your Abyss Artifacts and Power Cores, then this is the mod for you. While this is technically a mod that "cheats" the game, you still have to work for your Abyss items in the form of acquiring enough silver to purchase them. With this mod, you can find Abyss items at the Grocery shop in Hernand, and the regular artifacts cost nearly 30 silver. The mod simply speeds up the rate at which you can use Abyss Artifacts, as long as you have enough money. </p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Infinite Spirit and Spirit Regen</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1745/17457013/4676732-222f9b70e4bd689ca327d4cbdf660e07.jpg" /><br /><ul><li><strong>Created by</strong>: PhorgeForge</li><li><strong>Download</strong>: <a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/135">Nexus Mods</a><a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/303"><br /></a></li></ul><p>Spirit is an incredibly valuable resource in Crimson Desert, but you don't have an infinite supply of it and when you run out, it can take a while to fully resupply. Well, with the Infinite Spirit and Spirit Regen mod, you never have to worry about Spirit again. You now have an endless supply of it, meaning you can use your Spirit attacks and mechanics as much as you want.</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Gild's Gear</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1745/17457013/4676733-image_1775145769613.jpg" /><br /><ul><li><strong>Created by</strong>: Gild</li><li><strong>Download</strong>: <a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/384">Nexus Mods</a></li></ul><p>The Gild's Gear mod acts as a one-stop shop for all gear-related items in Crimson Desert. It replaces the General Store in Hernand and offers a variety of rare and high-quality armor and weapons. In addition to that, you can also buy Abyss Gears, crafting materials, food, treasure maps, and just about everything else you'd want in a playthrough. Essentially, you can completely kit Kliff out from the very start of the game, forgoing the need to track everything down yourself.</p></p><br/>     <p><h2>Infinite Dragon ATAG</h2><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1745/17457013/4676734-image_1775145831922.jpg" /><br /><ul><li><strong>Created by</strong>: PLMOST</li><li><strong>Download</strong>: <a href="https://www.nexusmods.com/crimsondesert/mods/238">Nexus Mods</a></li></ul><p>The dragon in Crimson Desert is arguably one of the best aspects of the entire game. However, when you unlock the dragon as a mount, you'll come to realize that it operates on a cooldown system. This means you can only use the dragon for preset amounts of time. Well, with the Infinite Dragon ATAG mod, that becomes obsolete. The mod allows you to purchase a Dragon ATAG cooldown reset item from Hernand, which makes it so you never have to wait for the cooldown to end. You can keep recalling the dragon as frequently as you want, giving you full-time access to the mount.</p></p><br/> ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"2900-7650";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 03:05:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:134:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1745/17457013/4676705-crimson-desert-new-trailer-gamescom-opening-night-live-2023.png";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:13;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"Fanatical&#039;s New Wholesome Collection Includes Up To 18 Cozy PC Games";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:165:"https://www.gamespot.com/articles/fanaticals-build-your-own-wholesome-collection-lets-you-bundle-some-great-cozy-games-on-the-cheap/1100-6539171/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3170:"<p>Looking for your next chill and cozy gaming session? Look no further than <a href="https://clicks.trx-hub.com/xid/fandom_32094_gamespot?q=https%3A%2F%2Fredirect.viglink.com%3Fkey%3Dfbff19622bfc4d759c94ca50d964e98d%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.fanatical.com%252Fen%252Fpick-and-mix%252Fbuild-your-own-wholesome-collection&p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Ffeeds%2Fmashup&event_type=click">Fanatical's Build Your Own Wholesome Collection bundle</a>. Like previous Fanatical bundles, you choose from a curated list of games, and the more you add to your bundle, the more you'll save. With the Build Your Own Wholesome bundle, there are 18 games to pick from. The deal starts at 3 games for $10, and you can pick any of the available games. If you want 5 games or more, they'll discount to $3 per game, and if you get 7+ games, they'll drop to $2.85 per game. If you grab all 18 games, that's a $277.82 total value for just $51.30.</p><div title="" data-embed-type="buylink" data-ref-id="undefined" data-template="undefined" data-size="buylink__small" data-title="" data-collection="%7B%22text%22:%22See%20at%20Fanatical%22,%22monetizedUrl%22:%22%22,%22rawUrl%22:%22https://redirect.viglink.com?key=fbff19622bfc4d759c94ca50d964e98d&amp;u=https://www.fanatical.com/en/pick-and-mix/build-your-own-wholesome-collection%22%7D" class="norewrite">           <a href="https://clicks.trx-hub.com/xid/fandom_32094_gamespot?q=https%3A%2F%2Fredirect.viglink.com%3Fkey%3Dfbff19622bfc4d759c94ca50d964e98d%26u%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.fanatical.com%2Fen%2Fpick-and-mix%2Fbuild-your-own-wholesome-collection&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Ffeeds%2Fmashup&event_type=click">See at Fanatical</a> </div><p>We have a detailed breakdown of all 18 games at the end of this article, but for fans of specific genres, we'll break down what you can expect. For puzzle fans, Dogpile is an adorable match-two game where, when you put together two matching dogs, they'll combine into one, much bigger dog. As a dog lover, this game alone was enough to get me to whip out my wallet. There's also Escape from Mystwood Mansion, a first-person puzzle game that (you guessed it) sees an attempt to escape from the creepy Mystwood Mansion by deciphering codes and solving riddles.</p><p>For you RPG heads, Rekindled Trails is a quaint adventure game with light RPG mechanics that emphasizes exploration, fishing, cooking, mining, and pretty much anything else you'd expect from the genre. You'll also solve puzzles and help rebuild the various towns of Aurteris after a calamity. If you prefer a more traditional fantasy flavor of RPG, Swords 'n Magic and Stuff is a relaxing open-world co-op game where you and a few friends can delve into dungeons using one of six different character classes. There are over 1,500 items to loot and kit your characters out with, and like any good cozy game, it has plenty of crafting and sim mechanics for you to rest your feet after a long day adventuring.</p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/fanaticals-build-your-own-wholesome-collection-lets-you-bundle-some-great-cozy-games-on-the-cheap/1100-6539171/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f/">Continue Reading at GameSpot</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"1100-6539171";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 06 Apr 2026 15:58:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:84:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1701/17013431/4678336-wholesome.jpg";s:4:"type";s:10:"image/jpeg";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:14;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"Get 15 PC Games For $15 And Support Charity With This Humble Bundle";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:131:"https://www.gamespot.com/articles/get-15-games-for-15-and-support-charity-with-this-humble-bundle/1100-6539170/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2233:"<p dir="ltr">Humble has just unveiled one of its best Humble Bundles ever in terms of pure bang-for-buck: The Humble 15 for $15 Bundle is <a href="https://clicks.trx-hub.com/xid/fandom_32094_gamespot?q=https%3A%2F%2Fredirect.viglink.com%3Fkey%3Dfbff19622bfc4d759c94ca50d964e98d%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.humblebundle.com%252Fgames%252Fhumble-15-for-15-spring-2026%26cuid%3D--&p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Ffeeds%2Fnews%2F&event_type=click">now available on Humble's official website</a>, and as the name suggests, it gives players access to a total of 15 PC games (a $158 value) for just $15. Even better, proceeds from sales of this bundle go to <a href="https://www.comicrelief.com/">Comic Relief</a>, a UK-based charity that helps connect families living in impoverished communities with healthy food, doctor's visits, and after-school programs.</p><div title="" data-embed-type="buylink" data-ref-id="undefined" data-template="undefined" data-size="buylink__small" data-title="" data-collection="%7B%22text%22:%22See%20at%20Humble%22,%22monetizedUrl%22:%22%22,%22rawUrl%22:%22https://redirect.viglink.com?key=fbff19622bfc4d759c94ca50d964e98d&amp;u=https://www.humblebundle.com/games/humble-15-for-15-spring-2026&amp;cuid=--%22%7D" class="norewrite">           <a href="https://clicks.trx-hub.com/xid/fandom_32094_gamespot?q=https%3A%2F%2Fredirect.viglink.com%3Fkey%3Dfbff19622bfc4d759c94ca50d964e98d%26u%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.humblebundle.com%2Fgames%2Fhumble-15-for-15-spring-2026%26cuid%3D--&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Ffeeds%2Fnews%2F&event_type=click">See at Humble</a> </div><p dir="ltr"> </p><p dir="ltr">Unlike most Humble Bundles, the 15 For $15 Game Bundle doesn't feature a pay-what-you-want option or tiered pricing, though players can pay more than $15 to donate additional funds to Comic Relief. Instead, you pay just $15 for the full 15 game collection. The bundle will be available until April 15, and all games in the bundle are delivered as official Steam keys that must be redeemed before they expire on April 17, 2027.</p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/get-15-games-for-15-and-support-charity-with-this-humble-bundle/1100-6539170/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f/">Continue Reading at GameSpot</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"1100-6539170";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 06 Apr 2026 15:50:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:12:"relatedGames";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"url";s:84:"https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1752/17528202/4676378-distraint.jpg";s:4:"type";s:10:"image/jpeg";s:5:"width";s:3:"480";s:6:"height";s:3:"270";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:4:"href";s:37:"https://www.gamespot.com/feeds/mashup";s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:"type";i:128;s:7:"headers";a:17:{s:4:"date";s:29:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 17:36:34 GMT";s:12:"content-type";s:30:"application/xml; charset=utf-8";s:14:"content-length";s:5:"16857";s:6:"server";s:10:"cloudflare";s:6:"cf-ray";s:20:"9e8acb97ce29f96a-DUS";s:15:"cf-cache-status";s:3:"HIT";s:13:"accept-ranges";s:5:"bytes";s:13:"cache-control";s:20:"public, max-age=1200";s:16:"content-encoding";s:4:"gzip";s:7:"expires";s:29:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 17:56:34 GMT";s:13:"last-modified";s:29:"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 17:17:58 GMT";s:25:"strict-transport-security";s:44:"max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload";s:4:"vary";s:15:"Accept-Encoding";s:9:"x-varnish";s:10:"459597 351";s:10:"set-cookie";s:278:"__cf_bm=bcAGz2bC1lN6G4MZ0F2wJc8kcPjerJPbAMVk.RbNcfY-1775583394-1.0.1.1-bz.Xq3rzIfbhwg5pbBFiOxjcOdkpWKrvuUfp83w0BcdNLoWgek1EuIuy6xKOBuEE6ijKntZkE8Be0pM4MIAvSSmjwBOg_NtLoOG33gdn2x0; path=/; expires=Tue, 07-Apr-26 18:06:34 GMT; domain=.gamespot.com; HttpOnly; Secure; SameSite=None";s:13:"server-timing";s:55:"cfCacheStatus;desc="HIT", cfOrigin;dur=0, cfEdge;dur=72";s:15:"referrer-policy";s:26:"no-referrer-when-downgrade";}s:5:"build";i:1760643936;s:21:"cache_expiration_time";i:1775586994;s:23:"__cache_expiration_time";i:1775586994;}